## Gaps
Better Auth’s exact callback/hook API for blocking sign-in by email allowlist should be checked against the version installed in the project before implementation. Neon’s Better Auth product docs are beta and primarily Next/React oriented, so for SvelteKit it is safer to use Better Auth directly against Neon Postgres/Drizzle rather than assuming Neon’s hosted Auth SDK has first-class SvelteKit ergonomics.

## Recommendation
Choose **Better Auth + Drizzle adapter + Google provider**, backed by Neon Postgres. Implement allowlist/permissions in your Drizzle schema and enforce them during sign-in/signup plus in SvelteKit `event.locals`/server-load guards. Choose **Arctic** only for maximal control/minimal dependency; choose **Auth.js SvelteKit** mainly if you already know Auth.js or are migrating an existing Auth.js app.
